eNCA's Samkele Maseko is following the story. #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The ANC has withdrawn the motion of no-confidence against Joburg Mayor Herman Mashaba. The party will however table it again at the next Council sitting. The ANC wanted to remove Mashaba, saying the city is in a poor financial state. READ: Mashaba 'looks forward' to another no-confidence vote It's claimed to have the support of more than 140 councillors. In 2017, Mashaba survived a motion of no confidence, after the ANC claimed he had failed to adequately provide services to the city's residents.